Someone needs to be held to account for the dismal state of affairs at PRASA. Parliament’s financial watchdog says it will be calling on current – and former – PRASA board members to explain inefficiencies at the parastatal. eNCA’s Monique Mortlock has the details. #eNCA  CAPE TOWN - Someone needs to be held to account for the dismal state of affairs at PRASA. Parliament’s financial watchdog says it will be calling on current – and former – PRASA board members to explain inefficiencies at the parastatal. The Standing Committee on Public Accounts conducted an oversight visit of Cape Town’s rail infrastructure on Friday. eNCA’s Monique Mortlock has the details in the video above.